                <h1>Explore the Harlem Renaissance: A Cultural Awakening</h1>
                <p>The Harlem Renaissance was a vibrant cultural movement in the 1920s, centering on Harlem, New York. It marked a flourishing of African American art, literature, and music, giving voice to Black identity and creativity. Key figures included authors like Langston Hughes and Zora Neale Hurston, and musicians like Duke Ellington, leaving a lasting impact on American culture.</p>
